
[1]nightshade

   NIGHTSHADE, n. A plant of the genus Solanum. The deadly nightshade is
   of the genus Atropa; the American nightshade of the genus Phytolacea;
   the bastard nightshade of the genus Rivina; the enchanter's nightshade
   of the genus Circaea; the Malabar nightshade of the genus Basella; and
   the three-leaved nightshade of the genus Trillium.
